description.en: Used to record events relating to a particular Heritage Resource. Activities can be used to give context and meaning to the records of heritage assets or areas. They provide information on ‘how we know what we know’ (for example investigative activities or research and analysis) or on how a particular Heritage Asset or Area has been managed through time (management activities).

description.en:
Used to record complex human-made, or human conceived, sites, areas or landscapes. Areas can be anything from a simple prehistoric settlement site (evidenced by a few flint-working fragments) to large-scale, urban conservation areas incorporating multiple assets within a city. The use of Area or Heritage Asset will be a question of granularity.

For building complexes such as castles, prisons and airfields, Area may be used to record the footprint of the site, eg. the curtain wall and outer defences of a castle. This Area can then be used as the parent for multiple Heritage Asset records.

Areas can be anything from a simple prehistoric settlement site (evidenced by a few flint-working fragments) to large-scale, urban conservation areas incorporating multiple assets within a city. The use of Area or Heritage Asset will be a question of granularity.

description.en:
Defines information relating to the character of man made items of heritage significance as identified by the Portable Antiquities Scheme
Includes individual artefacts, architectural items, artefact assemblages, individual ecofacts and ecofact assemblages, and environmental samples.

subtitle.en: Defines information relating to the character of man made items of heritage significance as identified by the Portable Antiquities Scheme

description.en: Describes how to document the sources used in the compilation or enhancement of heritage assets. This information provides authority for the entries without which the entries have no substantiating evidence. The information also allows future users to trace the origin of a given entry and to avoid the inefficiency of re-examining sources that have already been checked.

subtitle.en: Covers documentation of references to bibliographic sources of information held outside of the information system.

description.en: Version 0.1; A model to represent activities and information related to the review and evaluation of proposed developments or alterations to a structure.  This model supposes that an official of a government agency must review proposed construction activities and determine whether the activities require conditions/mitigations to conform with local requirements.  This model allows for formal application review and informal (e.g.: pre-application) consultations.

subtitle.en: Used to record activities relating to the provision of advice with regards to planning applications which may affect the historic environment.

The Heritage Story creates a user-friendly story which helps place the assets in their context within the historic environment.

Used to record the details of historic aircraft which are either retained as heritage assets (eg. Museum exhibits or Gate Guardians) or have been identified through the discovery of associated crash sites. A heritage asset record should be created for the crash site where known.

description.en: Used to record areas of the historic landscape. Historic Landscape Characterization is a method of identifying and interpreting the varying historic character within an area that looks beyond individual heritage assets as it brings together an understanding of the whole landscape and townscape.
